    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\"><strong>Number Abbreviation:</strong><br><br><strong>Given a positive integer <var>n</var> as input:</strong><br><strong>The goal</strong> is to abbreviate the <var>n</var> by representing it in a shorter format with a letter suffix to denote its magnitude (This abbreviation makes it easier to read the number).<br><strong>For example:</strong> input: <const>56324867</const> / output: <const>56.3M</const><br><br><strong>The abbreviation should follow the convention of using letters such as:</strong><br>&bull; <const>K</const> for thousands.<br>&bull; <const>M</const> for millions.<br>&bull; <const>B</const> for billions.<br>&bull; <const>T</const> for trillions.<br>&bull; If <var>n</var> is less than <const>1000</const>, then don't apply any change.<br><br><strong>In case <var>n</var> has been abbreviated (<var>n</var> &ge; 1000), the output should be like this:</strong><br>&bull; If the abbreviated number has a decimal part other than zero: <strong>round it</strong> to the nearest tenth.<br>&bull; If the abbreviated number is a whole number, <strong>remove the decimal and trailing zero</strong>.<br>&bull; Append the appropriate letter suffix <const>K</const>, <const>M</const>, <const>B</const>, or <const>T</const> to the abbreviation.<br>Eg. <const>564.2B</const>, <const>23.6T</const>, <const>76M</const> ...<br><br><strong>Tip:</strong><br>Begin by writing the fundamental parts of the program. As you go through the different test cases, you can fix any errors that occur in specific edge cases.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> A positive integer <var>n</var>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>Line 1 :</strong> The abbreviated form of <var>n</var>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">0 &le; <var>n</var> &le; 500,000,000,000,000 (aka. 0 &le; <var>n</var> &le; 500 Trillion)</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">67348782</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">67.3M</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
